<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-065-392  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 065 392.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 31 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM Japan's small laptop. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   IBM Japan Ltd. (product introduction).andO;Product:   IBM 5499 Online Note (Portable computer) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Computer industryHand-held computersProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM JAPAN'S SMALL LAPTOP TOKYO, JAPAN, 1989 OCT 19 (NB) -- IBM Japan hasreleased a portable, book-size computer with which can be used to communicatewith IBM's larger machines or online systems.andM;The IBM 5499 Online Note, with 2 kilogram weight, adopts an 8 megahertz80C186 processor at its heart, a standard 640-kilobyte main memory, and ablack and white LCD (liquid crystal display) screen with 640 by 400 pixels,capable of displaying 25 lines.andP;  Its special software, such as wordprocessors and scheduling, or software developed on its PS/55 personalcomputer, can be put into an IC (integrated circuit) memory card.andP;  Thebattery runs for about 3.5 hours with one charge.andM;MS-DOS Version 3.2, Kana-Kanji conversion program, dictionary, and fonts areincluded in ROM (read only memory).andM;The built-in modem enables communication between the machine and IBM's AS/400large computer or PS/55.andP;  The price with a 1200 bps (bits per second) modemand a 128 kilobyte RAM (random access memory) is 198,000 yen or $1,400, and a2400 bps modem and a 256 kilobyte RAM is 248,000 yen or $1,750.andP;  The shippingdate for the former is at the end of this month, and the latter is on the27th of December.andM;IBM Japan has entrusted Ricoh to produce the book-size computer which itoriginally developed.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19891026)</TEXT></DOC>